history.content: I have seen you on the time conflict form but am unable to enroll you because the class is full. Keep completing the form every 3 days and if/when space becomes available I will manually enroll you. I will process the form again tomorrow morning.

children.subject: Yes. I'm on 1st position of CS 168 waitlist for three weeks and I'm still not enrolled in the class by now.

Perhaps not last on the list but the system will never allow you to automatically enroll as long as you have a time conflict. Additional effort to complete a form (and manual over ride of the conflict by someone behind the scenes) will always be the case. When you complete the form and if there are open seats when the form is processed will determine when you get into the class.
Alright, I just want to make sure: having a schedule conflict is equivalent to being always last on the waitlist? There's no way to fix this other than by waiting or fixing the conflict?

history.content:
Hello, I am attempting to enroll in CS 194-26 and I am 1st on the waitlist. I have a schedule conflict with the INFO 159 lecture at the same time. The special CS conflict form does not help me since I am being bypassed during automatic waitlist processing (with no SIS Central prompts to override) while the class will always be full during manual waitlist processing. Is this intended behavior? How do I fix this situation?

EDIT: I do not want a swap, I need both courses.
history.subject: Bypassed on Waitlist by Schedule Conflict
